The paper deals with the approximability of Max-CSPs, which is a central topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). It also involves the study of distributions and pseudo-randomness, which are important topics in computer science theory (cs.DS). The paper introduces a relaxed notion of an approximate solution, which involves the use of algorithms, making it relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also includes examples and results related to geometric constraints, which falls under computational geometry (cs.CG). Finally, the paper discusses the distribution of k-bit strings, which is related to information theory (cs.IT).
